name: indeterminable
content:
Add to word list
Add to word list
If something is indeterminable, it cannot be decided or the facts about it cannot be discovered: The court decided that the cause of the accident was indeterminable due to the lack of evidence. Exactly how many different uses this product could have is indeterminable.
More examplesFewer examplesMost people agree that the impact that the policy will have is indeterminable.He spoke very loudly and with a strong but indeterminable accent.I was greeted by a cheerful-looking woman of indeterminable age.
